curam.util.client.model

Class FieldParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractMap<K,V>
      • java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
        • curam.util.client.model.internal.DefaultComponentParameters
          • curam.util.client.model.FieldParameters
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ComponentParameters, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>

    public class FieldParameters
extends curam.util.client.model.internal.DefaultComponentParameters

    The parameters to a Field that can be used to influence the rendering of the field. Unlike the configuration for the domain renderer that will apply to all fields targeting server interface properties associated with a particular domain definition, the field parameters are specific to each instance of a field. Parameters include those defining the label and tooltip text for the field, the width of the field, whether or not it is mandatory to enter a value in an input field, etc.

    The parameters are provided as a read-only map of name/value pairs. Many parameters correspond directly to attributes of the UIM FIELD element. Field attributes that are set to their default values in UIM are not usually defined as parameters of the Field to be rendered, so if the value of a parameter is null, you can choose whether or not to apply a default value. For convenience, the FieldParameters.getWithDefault(String) method can be used to get the parameter value and automatically return a default value (if applicable) when the parameter is not defined.

    This class defines constants for the standard parameters that are supported for a field and provides their default values. These constants should be used when referring to the parameters to protect against name changes.

      • TOOLTIP

        public static final java.lang.String TOOLTIP
        The value to use as the tooltip for the field. This usually combines the field's label and description with other text such as the word "mandatory" and is a more verbose label that can be used to support accessibility requirements. If not defined, the default value (returned using FieldParameters.getWithDefault(String)) will be the value of the "LABEL" parameter, which may not itself be set.
        See Also:

      • getWithDefault

        public java.lang.String getWithDefault(java.lang.String name)
        Gets the value of the parameter, or its default value if the parameter is not defined. Not all parameters have default values, so null may be returned. The default for some parameters (like "TOOLTIP") may be the value of another parameter (the "LABEL" value in the case of the "TOOLTIP" parameter).
        Specified by:
        getWithDefault in interface ComponentParameters
        Overrides:
        getWithDefault in class curam.util.client.model.internal.DefaultComponentParameters
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the parameter.
        Returns:
        The value of the parameter, or its default value if the parameter is not defined.
